Package com.compendium.core.datamodel

Interface Summary
ICode The Code object represents a tag in Project Compendium.
IExtendedNodeType NOTE: THIS CLASS IS NOT BEING USED YET AND IS NOT COMPLETED
IGroup NOTE: THIS CLASS IS NOT BEING USED YET AND IS THEREFORE NOT COMPLETED The IGroup interface is provided for the Group object.
IIdObject The IdObject is the generic project compendium object used as the basis for any object that requires a unique identification.
ILink A Link represents a relationship between two nodes.
IModel IModel Class is the interface to the Model class which is the base class for the object cache for a given database and also holds a set of the database service objects.
INodeDetailPage The INodeDetailPage holds the information for a page of node detail text
INodePosition The INodePosition object defines the position of a node in a view.
INodeSummary The Node object represents a hyperlinkable node that has as its minimum properties a type, label and detailed description.
IPCObject The IPCObject defines the interface for a remote project compendium object.
IPCSession The Node object represents a hyperlinkable node that has as its minimum properties a type, label and detailed description.
IPermission The IPermission interface is provided for the Permission object.
IShortCutNodeSummary The ShortCutNodeSummary object represents a short cut to a Node in the system.
IUserProfile This interface represents a project compendium user profile
IView The IView is an interface object that represents a collection of nodes and links.
 

Class Summary
Code The Code object represents a tag in Project Compendium.
CodeCache This object store all the code and code groups information.
ExtendedNodeType NOTE: THIS CLASS IS NOT BEING USED YET AND IS NOT COMPLETED
ExternalConnection The ExternalConnection object represents a connection to a MySQL database, or Jabber Server, or such.
Favorite The Favorite object holds information about a user favorite / Bookmark item.
Group NOTE: THIS CLASS IS NOT BEING USED YET AND IS THEREFORE NOT COMPLETED The Group object represents the a group that belongs to a project a user with administrator priviledges can modify properties for a group object when a single administrator is modifying the groups, other administrators cannot access the data
IdObject The IdObject is the generic compendium object used as the basis for any object that requires a unique identification.
Link A Link represents a relationship between two nodes.
MediaIndex The MediaIndex object defines the media timestamp offset of a node in a view in a specific meeting.
Meeting Meeting defines the data object for storing meeting data, such as name, date, attendees, agenda etc.
Model Model Class is the base class for the object cache for a given database and also holds a set of the database service objects and project level preference settings.
NodeCache This object store the nodes and views being used in the current session
NodeDetailPage The NodeDetailPage holds the information for a page of node detail text.
NodePosition The INodePosition object defines the position of a node in a view.
NodeSummary The Node object represents a hyperlinkable node that has as its minimum properties a type, label and detailed description.
PCObject The PCObject defines a compendium object.
PCSession The Node object represents a hyperlinkable node that has as its minimum properties a type, label and detailed description.
Permission THIS CLASS IS NOT CURRENTLY USED The Permission object represents the permission for a group to an object in the database representing a pc compendium object.
ShortCutNodeSummary The ShortCutNodeSummary object represents a short cut to a Node in the system.
UserProfile This class represents a Compendium user profile Author Rema Natarajan / Michelle Bachler
View The View object is a node that represents a collection of nodes and links.
ViewLayer The ViewLayer object holds additional information about the visual state of a JInternalFrame with a View inside.
ViewProperty The ViewProperty object holds additional information about the visual state of a JInternalFrame with a View inside.
Workspace The Workspace object represents a collection of open views, thier positions, size and state (icon/maximized).
WorkspaceView The WorkspaceView object represents a open ViewFrames in Compendium with scrollbar positions and reference to child View Note: This class is a holding container only and does not currently write to the database
 

Exception Summary
ModelSessionException Signals that the model or session objects were found to be null.
